HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1320
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Firefighter Matthew
McDowell of the Signal Mountain Fire
Department for his heroism.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should honor those
individuals who, during the course of their duties, endeavor to protect the lives of their fellow
citizens, braving great dangers and putting themselves at risk to save others; and
WHEREAS, Firefighter Matthew McDowell of the Signal Mountain Fire Department
Green Shift was truly heroic in his response to an emergency situation on October 15, 2025,
helping to save the life of a citizen in peril; and
WHEREAS, on that date, Firefighter McDowell and his fellow crew members responded
to a cardiac arrest at a local residence, where immediate and decisive action was required to
preserve life; and
WHEREAS, through their exceptional training and coordinated efforts, the team provided
critical care to the patient, stabilizing her condition and ensuring she received the urgent
medical attention necessary for survival; and
WHEREAS, as a result of these efforts, the patient was released from the hospital just
days later with a full recovery and no neurological deficits; and
WHEREAS, Firefighter McDowell's quick thinking and compassionate action were
invaluable in helping to bring about a positive outcome in a potentially deadly situation; and
WHEREAS, it is wholly fitting that we recognize Firefighter Matthew McDowell for his
exceptional act of heroism; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Firefighter Matthew McDowell of the Signal Mountain Fire
